                  <decoDesc>
                    <summary>Miniatures, all in the late 20th century hand of the “speckled garment artist,” painted over text</summary>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d01">
                        <locus target="#iv"/>
                        <desc>Moses, with the tablet, <persName ref="PRS1002Aaron"/> and the Holy Spirit (<persName ref="PRS10774Paraq"/>) <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1024MosesLaw"/>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d02">
                        <locus target="#iir"/>
                        <desc>The Holy Trinity surrounded by the Four Living Creatures <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1030Trinity"/>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d03">
                        <locus target="#iiv"/>
                        <desc>
                           <persName ref="PRS4585Georgeo"/> and the <term key="dragon"/>, <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1035HolyMan"/>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d04">
                        <locus target="#iiir"/>
                        <desc>The Madonna and Child, <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1031VirginAndChild"/>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d05">
                        <locus target="#iiiv"/>
                        <desc>Jesus Carrying the Cross and being Flogged, <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1065RoadtoCalvary"/>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d06">
                        <locus target="#ivr"/>
                        <desc>The Crucifixion <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1005Crucifixion"/>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d07">
                        <locus target="#ivv"/>
                        <desc>David playing the harp, <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1066DavidHarp"/>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d08">
                        <locus target="#194r"/>
                        <desc>The Resurrection, Raising Adam and Eve, <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1008Descent"/>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d09">
        Decorative designs:   <locus target="#1r #9r #17v #27v #40r #49v #57r #68r #81v #92r #99r #114r #129r #133r #140v #148v #164r #173r"/>
        (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ሐረግ፡</foreign> using black, red, purple, green, yellow and blue); no <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሐረግ፡</foreign> marks the beginning of the Gate of Light
      </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                    <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#8v #91v"/> Glorification of the Trinity (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ስብሐት፡ ለአብ፡</foreign>
                           and prayer to Mary asking her intercession (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰእሊ፡ ለነ፡</foreign>).
                        </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <desc>
                          Overlooked words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#98v #165r #184v"/>);
                          and overlooked lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#52v #55v #95v #130r #151r #166r #167r #167v #168r #168v #169r #169v #170r #170v #171r #171v #172r #172v #175r"/>)
                        </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#ir #194v"/> blank.
                        </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc>
                          This scribe has avoided the problem of lines of text too long to fit on one line by adopting an aspect ratio that leaves ample
                          room for the width of most lines. When the line would have been too long, the scribe finishes the end of the line with words
                          written smaller so as to avoid leftover text (e.g., <locus target="#16v #17r #29r #30r #42r"/>, etc.). Also, the scribe may
                          complete the line above the end of the line (e.g., <locus target="#2v #6v #10r #19r #19v #20v #27v"/>, etc.).
                        </desc>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                  </additions>
